Under the contract, the same concern was entrusted with the technological equipment of the plant, the training of specialists.[14][15]
On January 3, 1967, the Central Committee of the All-Union Leninist Young Communist League announced the construction of the Volga Automobile Plant of the All-Union Shock Komsomol
construction site. Thousands of people, mostly young people, went to Tolyatti to build an auto giant. Already on January 21, 1967
year, the first cubic meter of land was dug for the construction of the first workshop of the plant - the building of auxiliary workshops (KVTs).[14][15]
Since 1969, labor collectives of the plant began to form, most of them were people who built the plant.